    "body": "### Problem\n\n```\n:edit foo/bar/baz.tx\n:update ++p\n```\n\nBuffer is not written and the `foo/bar/` directory is not created.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`:update` should work on a new, empty buffer, without having to make edits to the buffer to convince `:update` to write it.\n\nMaybe `bufIsChanged` should return true for new, empty buffers?\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/78f4994627b7d9c3b85f30028fe55ff38024a39d/src/nvim/undo.c#L3106-L3109",
